THE final 10 artists in the running to be named Worldwide Act at the 2014 MTV EMAs have been revealed. Nominees revealed for world act prize THE final 10 artists in the running to be named Worldwide Act at the 2014 MTV EMAs have been revealed.One Direction, Alessandra Amoroso and 5 Seconds of Summer are three of the hottest artists who will battle it out.After seven weeks, three stages of voting and millions of fan votes via mtvema.com, the competition has been narrowed down from 286 musical acts.The Worldwide Act winner will be revealed at the show, which will broadcast live to MTV channels worldwide from the SSE Hydro in Glasgow on Sunday, November 9 at 9pm.Fans can vote for their favourite artist online. 